Ifeanyi Uba’s Capital Oil & Gas Industries Limited sits atop the list of debtors recently release by the Asset Management Corporation of Nigeria (AMCON) with a whopping N115 billion.
According to AMCON, the list which included top 105 delinquent debtors is another way of bringing the crisis to the public after all avenues provided by the corporation for the debtors to propose acceptable resolution terms failed.
